Vice President Mike Pence gave a speech at MacAllister Machinery in Indianapolis, Indiana, urging Congress to pass the U.S.-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA). He highlighted the importance of trade for the state of Indiana and the benefits that the USMCA would bring, including job creation and economic growth. Pence also discussed the progress made under the Trump administration, such as tax cuts, deregulation, and the revival of the manufacturing industry. He called on the audience to reach out to their elected representatives and voice their support for the USMCA. Pence emphasized the need for bipartisan cooperation and unity in order to continue the economic success of the country.